The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 21 June is 281,261 (32,417 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 16 June, there were 1,551 new confirmed cases (178.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 09 June, there were 1,094 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 42% (457 extra cases).
